There are two different things that screw this up. That is, fix one of them (not both), and the problem is solved.

&lt;h1&gt;First&lt;/h1&gt;
I found that there is a problem with this block of CSS:

```
html, body {
  height: 100%;
}
```

It&#39;s the `html` tag that screws things up in iOS. When I get rid of it, iOS displays just like the other operating systems do.

I was using that block to keep the footer always down at the bottom.

&lt;h2&gt;Second&lt;/h2&gt;
The other problem is with this (class `.home` is only on the `body` element):

